Question:
Find the first string starting with "b" in a list.

Input:
List<String> list = Arrays.asList("apple", "banana", "cherry");

Solutions:-

Java 8 Streams find first "b"-starting string using filter + findFirst(). For input ["apple", "banana", "cherry"], returns "banana".

#Step-by-Step Logic
Stream list → filter(s -> s.startsWith("b")) → findFirst() → Optional.ifPresent print.

#Complete Implementation

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;

public class FirstStartingWithB {
    public static void findFirstB(List<String> list) {
        list.stream()
            .filter(s -> s.startsWith("b"))
            .findFirst()
            .ifPresent(System.out::println);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<String> list = Arrays.asList("apple", "banana", "cherry");
        findFirstB(list);
    }
}

Prints banana. Short-circuits at first match.

#Thought Process
filter predicate startsWith("b") case-sensitive. findFirst() deterministic, ordered, short-circuiting. ifPresent safe handling. Efficient O(n worst-case).

#Edge Cases Analysis
No match: Empty Optional, nothing prints.
Empty list: No match.
First element: Immediate return.
Null list: NPE.
Null elements: null.startsWith("b") NPE—filter nulls first.
Case: "Banana" false.
